HIGHWAYS: Urges and requests the Department of Transportation and Development to
conduct a traffic study to evaluate adding turn lanes onto Louisiana Highway 1024
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Department of Transportation and Development to conduct a traffic
3 study to evaluate the benefits and feasibility of adding turn lanes onto Louisiana
4 Highway 1024.
5 WHEREAS, according to the Louisiana Highway Safety Commission, turns at
6 intersections can cause delays and decrease safety; and
7 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Highway Safety Commission recommends installation
8 of dedicated left-turn and right-turn lanes, deceleration and acceleration lanes, and space to
9 handle turning traffic away from the through traffic will improve delays and increase safety
10 and efficiency; and
11 WHEREAS, installing turn lanes can significantly improve intersections; and
12 WHEREAS, common reasons for installing turn lanes are:
13 (1) Rates of speeds are too high to turn safely onto or away from a roadway.
14 (2) Patterns of rear-end, sideswipe, or weaving crashes when through vehicles
15 conflict with turning vehicles.
16 (3) Drivers have extended wait times to make a turn.
17 (4) A higher number of turning vehicles.
18 WHEREAS, improper turning and a lack of dedicated turn lanes cause a significant
19 portion of United States traffic accidents, with roughly 1.7 million crashes annually; and
