1 WHEREAS, intersections without dedicated left turn lanes are highly dangerous and
2 installing them can reduce total intersection accidents by approximately twenty to seventy-
3 six percent, depending on the roadway.
4 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
5 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Department of Transportation and
6 Development to conduct a traffic study to evaluate the benefits and feasibility of adding turn
7 lanes onto Louisiana Highway 1024.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation and
9 Development shall submit a written report detailing its findings for the benefits and
10 feasibility of adding turn lanes onto Louisiana Highway 1024 to the House Committee on
11 Transportation, Highways and Public Works prior to January 1, 2027.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
13 secretary of the Department of Transportation and Development.
